## The Null Assertion Operator

Adding an exclamation mark `!` to the end of a variable forcefully rips off the Nullable warning.

```dart
String? data = 'Hello World';

// Dart restricts this because data 'might' be null.
// print(data.length); 

// The '!' forces the compiler to treat it as a normal String.
print(data!.length); 
```
You are taking full legal responsibility for its safety.
